wering%20evergreens%20lining%20the%20way%20on%20either%20side%2C%20I%20couldn't%20help%20but%20wonder%20if%20I'd%20made%20the%20right%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20on%20my%20way%20to%20join%20my%20new%20fianc%C3%A9%20in%20San%20Antonio.%20We%20met%20at%20a%20concert%20in%20Seattle%20about%20a%20year%20before%2C%20and%20fell%20instantly%20in%20love.%20We%20danced%20most%20of%20the%20night%2C%20talked%20long%20after%20the%20lights%20went%20up%2C%20and%20planned%20our%20first%20date%20for%20the%20next%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20almost%20a%20year%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-distance-relationship-success-started-with-14-hour-date-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-distance%20romance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20proposed.%20I%20was%20over%20the%20moon%20and%20couldn't%20wait%20for%20us%20to%20be%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20only%20one%20problem%3A%20He%20still%20had%20a%20year%20to%20go%20before%20earning%20his%20undergraduate%20degree%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20San%20Antonio%2C%20and%20I%20was%20one%20year%20into%20my%20dream%20job%20in%20the%20marketing%20department%20at%20Pacific%20Northwest%20Ballet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a96d67e-7ace-4f5a-9a97-ce43e8b8d3b8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20starting%20my%20life%20in%20Texas%2C%20I%20made%20a%20few%20career%20moves%20and%20backup%20plans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225953%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20rolling%20mountains%20in%20%20Texas%20Panhandle%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fa1d1c38bee05c96983fec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223966%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETexas%20never%20quite%20felt%20like%20home%20to%20me%2C%20but%20I%20met%20some%20amazing%20people.%3Cp%3EHundley_Photography%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20my%20job%20and%20my%20coworkers%2C%20but%20I%20was%2031%2C%20and%20my%20biological%20clock%20was%20banging%20like%20a%20jackhammer.%20I'd%20always%20wanted%20a%20family%2C%20and%20didn't%20think%20I%20could%20stand%20another%20year%20away%20from%20the%20love%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20knew%20I%20was%20taking%20a%20risk%20giving%20up%20everything%20for%20someone%20I'd%20known%20for%20less%20than%20a%20year%2C%20and%20my%20friends%20were%20giving%20me%20the%20side%20eye%20over%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20before%20I%20called%20the%20moving%20company%2C%20I%20started%20my%20own%20boutique%20communications%20firm%2C%20landed%20my%20first%20big%20client%20in%20San%20Antonio%2C%20and%20told%20myself%20that%20if%20it%20didn't%20work%20out%2C%20I%20could%20always%20sell%20my%20engagement%20ring%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-nyc-to-seattle-only-lasted-one-year-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emove%20back%20to%20Seattle%3C%2Fa%3E%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20crossed%20the%20state%20line%20into%20Oregon%20with%20my%20cat%20Queenie%20next%20to%20me%20in%20her%20carrier%20and%20everything%20I%20owned%20crammed%20into%20my%20tiny%20Honda%20Civic%2C%20I%20felt%20anxious%2C%20eager%2C%20and%20excited%20to%20start%20my%20new%20life%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20believe%20my%20luck%20in%20already%20landing%20a%20juicy%20project%20with%20my%20first%20big%20client%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20San%20Antonio's%20leading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-public-relations-industry-moves-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epublic-relations%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20looked%20forward%20to%20meeting%20my%20new%20teammates%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20saw%20the%20move%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20connect%20with%20my%20roots%20since%20my%20dad's%20family%20was%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F180m-texas-ranch-gutted-largest-wildfire-in-state-history-owners-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETexas%20Panhandle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20lived%20there%20as%20a%20child.%20I%20looked%20forward%20to%20learning%20more%20about%20his%20home%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%20in%20San%20Antonio%20three%20days%20later%2C%20my%20fianc%C3%A9%20was%20waiting%20for%20me%20in%20our%20new%20apartment.%20He'd%20just%20picked%20up%20the%20keys%20earlier%20that%20day%2C%20and%20there%20wasn't%20a%20single%20piece%20of%20furniture%20in%20the%20entire%20place%2C%20so%20we%20slept%20in%20a%20sleeping%20bag%20on%20the%20floor.%20I%20was%20so%20happy%2C%20it%20might%20as%20well%20have%20been%20the%20Four%20Seasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20immediately%20jumped%20into%20my%20work%2C%20began%20networking%2C%20and%20started%20making%20friends.%20By%20July%2C%20I%20was%20pregnant%20with%20our%20first%20child%2C%20and%20nine%20months%20later%2C%20our%20daughter%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20baby%20girl%20was%20only%20a%20few%20weeks%20old%20when%20we%20learned%20that%20my%20new%20husband's%20company%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20while%20finishing%20school%2C%20planned%20to%20shut%20down%20their%20local%20plant%2C%20and%20he%20would%20be%20laid%20off%20within%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20was%20unsettling%2C%20but%20it%20coincided%20with%20my%20desire%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20my%20family%20on%20the%20West%20Coast%20now%20that%20I%20was%20a%20new%20mom.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20never%20felt%20totally%20at%20home%20in%20Texas.%20I%20missed%20the%20culture%2C%20natural%20beauty%2C%20and%20familiarity%20of%20the%20West%20Coast%20and%20couldn't%20wait%20to%20get%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f824031-a029-4297-a453-096ed00f2cc9%5C%22%3EWe%20didn't%20stay%20in%20Texas%20for%20very%20long%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20so%20glad%20I%20made%20the%20move%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20plants%20next%20to%20home%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0e125a7684ba33f7380e63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20a%20few%20months%2C%20I%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20West%20Coast%20with%20my%20now-husband%20and%20our%20daughter%3Cp%3EAmber%20Campbell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20just%20a%20few%20months%20after%20my%20then-husband%20graduated%20%E2%80%94%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20after%20I%20arrived%20in%20Texas%2C%20we%20packed%20a%20U-Haul%2C%20and%20headed%20west%20with%20our%206-month-old%20daughter%2C%20just%20like%20my%20grandmother%20did%20with%20my%20dad%2050%20years%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I'm%20surprised%20to%20see%20how%20much%20I%20gave%20up%20to%20move%20to%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20my%20dream%20job%2C%20a%20city%20I%20loved%2C%20and%20the%20life%20I'd%20built%20in%20Seattle.%20However%2C%20I'm%20also%20grateful%20for%20what%20I%20got%20in%20return%3A%20I%20had%20my%20daughter%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-a-business-according-to-successful-entrepreneurs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20a%20successful%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20scratch%20in%20a%20new%20city%2C%20and%20made%20dear%20friends%20I'm%20still%20in%20touch%20with%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20my%20dad's%20side%20of%20our%20family%2C%20like%20why%20they%20loved%20fried%20okra%20and%20said%20%26quot%3By'all%26quot%3B%20even%20though%20they%20lived%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20didn't%20last%2C%20and%20neither%20did%20the%20marriage%2C%20but%20my%20willingness%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-for-new-relationship-love-risky-best-decision-still-together-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erisk%20everything%20for%20love%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20even%20when%20it%20didn't%20work%20out%20the%20way%20I%20planned%20%E2%80%94%20is%20what%20made%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life%20possible.%20I'm%20still%20glad%20I%20got%20in%20my%20Honda%20Civic%20and%20drove%20south%20all%20those%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-texas-for-partner-returned-home-seattle-worth-it-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780319521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0e12cd7684ba33f7380e68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-texas-for-partner-returned-home-seattle-worth-it-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Although%20leaving%20my%20dream%20job%20in%20Seattle%20and%20living%20in%20Texas%20for%20a%20long-distance%20partner%20didn't%20work%20out%20perfectly%2C%20I%20don't%20regret%20moving%20for%20love.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Amber%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20Fired%20Record%208%2C150%20Drones%20At%20Ukraine%20In%20May%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Russia%20also%20fired%20211%20missiles%20in%20May%2C%20among%20the%20highest%20monthly%20figures%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Kyiv%20called%20on%20the%20United%20States%20for%20urgent%20help.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780319107000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-fired-record-8-150-drones-at-ukraine-in-may-report-11576263%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%20also%20fired%20211%20missiles%20in%20May%2C%20among%20the%20highest%20monthly%20figures%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Kyiv%20called%20on%20the%20United%20States%20for%20urgent%20help.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-fired-record-8-150-drones-at-ukraine-in-may-report-11576263%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com