20grew%20up.%20I%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20with%20my%20Utah%20salary%2C%20which%20was%20about%20%2438%2C000%20annually.%20I%20was%20broke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20still%20working%20that%20job%20%E2%80%94%20making%20about%20%2452%2C000%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20when%20I%20co-founded%20the%20podcast%20in%202018.%20Right%20away%2C%20my%20day-to-day%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-financial-planner-young-people-anxious-about-money-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20evaporated.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20put%20money%20into%20a%20savings%20account%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20I%20was%20more%20social%20because%20I%20didn't%20need%20to%20choose%20between%20buying%20drinks%20and%20paying%20for%20dinner.%20It%20was%20freeing%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20financially%20very%20comfortable%20and%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e201a93e-37db-49c4-8d41-113d23899e6f%5C%22%3EI%20lost%20my%20identity%20and%20didn't%20trust%20myself%20after%20leaving%20the%20podcast%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20safety%20disappeared%20seemingly%20overnight.%20In%202020%2C%20I%20had%20a%20very%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falix-earle-alex-cooper-feud-who-winning-social-media-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efallout%20with%20my%20cofounder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Alex%2C%20and%20left%20the%20show%20after%20contract%20negotiations%20fell%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20job%20that%20had%20become%20my%20identity%2C%20and%20I%20was%20very%20proud%20of%20that.%20Within%20days%2C%20my%20job%2C%20my%20identity%2C%20and%20my%20income%20were%20completely%20gone.%20My%20relationship%20with%20Alex%20was%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20massive%20change%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20found%20myself%20trying%20to%20reconcile%20what%20had%20happened%20while%20also%20viewing%20it%20through%20a%20very%20public%20narrative.%20That%20was%20tricky.%20I%20became%20very%20untrusting.%20I%20didn't%20even%20trust%20myself.%20Everything%20I%20thought%20was%20real%20had%20disappeared%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20numb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20I%20leaned%20on%20my%20family.%20My%20mom%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agent-side-hustle-franchised-coffee-shop-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%20agent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20my%20dad%20owned%20a%20construction%20business%2C%20so%20during%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%2C%20we%20went%20from%20being%20financially%20OK%20to%20a%20tough%20spot.%20I%20knew%20I%20could%20be%20scrappy.%20I%20also%20knew%20that%20they%20understood%20who%20I%20was%2C%20outside%20the%20public%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4679da0-953f-4947-8331-3354bf616057%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20negotiate%20a%20new%20career%20while%20feeling%20worthless%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20be%20the%20kind%20of%20person%20who%20carefully%20considered%20every%20decision%2C%20weighing%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20and%20making%20risk%20assessments.%20After%20leaving%20the%20podcast%2C%20I%20had%20to%20go%20with%20my%20gut.%20I%20knew%20time%20was%20of%20the%20essence%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20push%20forward%20without%20fully%20knowing%20what%20I%20was%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20interesting%20experience%20negotiating%20my%20worth%20at%20a%20time%20when%20I%20felt%20worthless.%20Even%20though%20I%20lost%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20my%20identity%2C%20I%20had%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20self%20that%20my%20mom%20instilled.%20That%20helped%20me%20as%20I%20formed%20my%20own%20podcast%2C%20%26quot%3BSofia%20with%20an%20F%2C%26quot%3B%20later%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20said%20very%20little%20about%20the%20fallout%20from%20%26quot%3BCall%20Her%20Daddy.%26quot%3B%20Early%20on%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20this%20was%20too%20massive%20%E2%80%94%20within%20my%20life%20and%20the%20public%20discussion%20%E2%80%94%20to%20respond%20to%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e043109-9f78-4716-8e9d-7d8bb71a02c6%5C%22%3EI've%20learned%20it's%20important%20to%20talk%20about%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20I've%20been%20very%20careful%20to%20make%20sure%20my%20identity%20isn't%20fully%20wrapped%20up%20in%20my%20job.%20My%20identity%20is%20built%20around%20my%20morals%2C%20my%20values%2C%20and%20how%20I%20treat%20people.%20Every%20so%20often%2C%20I%20ask%20myself%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20all%20of%20this%20is%20gone%20tomorrow%2C%20how%20are%20you%20going%20to%20feel%3F%26quot%3B%20That%20impacts%20my%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20an%20open%20book.%20After%20so%20much%20was%20said%20about%20me%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20didn't%20have%20much%20to%20lose%20by%20staying%20in%20the%20public%20eye.%20The%20only%20thing%20I'm%20private%20about%20is%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-youre-in-a-strong-relationship-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eromantic%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20joked%20that%20I%20would%20ask%20to%20see%20guys'%20bank%20accounts%20on%20the%20first%20date.%20It%20was%20said%20in%20jest%2C%20but%20there%20was%20some%20truth%20to%20it.%20I%20didn't%20ask%20to%20see%20my%20now-fianc%C3%A9e's%20account%20when%20we%20met%20%E2%80%94%20though%20that%20would%20have%20been%20funny.%20However%2C%20we%20have%20been%20open%20about%20money%20from%20the%20start%2C%20and%20I'll%20say%20I'm%20a%20firm%20believer%20in%20prenups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20seen%20how%20money%20discussions%20can%20go%20wrong%2C%20and%20I%20know%20it's%20very%20important%20to%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-fighting-about-money-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopen%20dialogue%20about%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsofia-franklyn-call-her-daddy-fallout-career-202