to%20be%20the%20most%20expensive%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20does%20that%20actually%20mean%20for%20fans%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20tournament%2C%20Business%20Insider%20crunched%20the%20numbers%20to%20game%20out%20how%20much%20it%20would%20cost%20a%20fan%20to%20follow%20their%20home%20team%20through%20the%20biggest%20sporting%20event%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20booking%20websites%20and%20publicly%20available%20information%20from%20host%20cities%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewe%20calculated%20how%20much%20a%20fan%20would%20spend%20to%20attend%20the%20event%20based%20on%20four%20data%20points%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftickets%2Ffifa-world-cup-2026-ticket-resale-prices-dates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20each%20game%20ticket%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20flights%2C%20hotels%2C%20and%20local%20transit.%20All%20flight%2C%20ticket%2C%20and%20hotel%20data%20was%20gathered%20in%20early%20May%3B%20a%20fan's%20true%20spend%20could%20fluctuate%20if%20they%20book%20earlier%20or%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2048%20teams%20competing%20in%20this%20year's%20World%20Cup.%20The%20event%20runs%20for%20roughly%20five%20weeks%2C%20from%20June%2011%20to%20July%2019.%20To%20narrow%20down%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20experiment%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20follow%20the%20finalists%20of%20the%20last%20tournament%20and%20two%20big%20favorites%20for%20the%202026%20tournament%3A%20Argentina%20and%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%3F%20Get%20ready%20to%20spend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20that%20a%20dedicated%20Argentina%20fan%20could%20have%20to%20shell%20out%20over%20%2430%2C000%20to%20follow%20their%20team%20the%20whole%20way%20through%20the%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d314a6f7-624f-4086-a5c2-ef106320e896%5C%22%3EAttending%20the%20group%20stage%20will%20run%20close%20to%20%2410%2C000%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20team%20competing%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%20is%20guaranteed%20to%20play%20its%20first%20three%20games%2C%20no%20matter%20if%20they%20win%20or%20lose.%20This%20is%20called%20the%20group%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArgentina%20plays%20its%20opening%20match%20in%20Kansas%20City%2C%20followed%20by%20two%20games%20in%20Dallas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20our%20calculations%20and%20including%20game%20tickets%2C%20hotel%20rooms%2C%20flight%20tickets%2C%20and%20local%20transit%2C%20it%20would%20cost%20a%20fan%20from%20Argentina%20about%20%249%2C800%20to%20see%20all%20three%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20breakdown%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20there%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20flight%20from%20the%20Argentine%20capital%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuenos-aires-surprising-things-first-trip-american-argentina-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuenos%20Aires%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20cheapest%20available%20to%20Kansas%20City%20with%20a%20maximum%20of%20one%20layover%20was%20over%20%241%2C300%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-united-best-airline-first-class-travel-frequent-traveler-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FR0Xs7%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20showing%20the%20costs%20to%20see%20Argentina's%20three%20World%20Cup%202026%20group%20stage%20games%2C%20broken%20down%20into%20the%20flight%2C%20game%20ticket%2C%20hotel%2C%20and%20local%20transit.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FR0Xs7%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20cheapest%20three-star%20hotel%20in%20the%20host%20city's%20downtown%20area%2C%20trying%20to%20keep%20the%20budget%20relatively%20affordable%20without%20sacrificing%20comfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20nights%20in%20Kansas%20City%20would%20cost%20about%20%241%2C800%2C%20and%20eight%20nights%20in%20Dallas%20would%20cost%20over%20%243%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20the%20game%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20looked%20at%20the%20cheapest%20seats%20available%20in%20early%20May%2C%20and%20found%20it%20would%20cost%20%24747%20for%20the%20game%20in%20Kansas%20City%20against%20Algeria%2C%20%24835%20for%20the%20first%20game%20in%20Dallas%20against%20Austria%2C%20and%20%24862%20for%20the%20final%20game%20against%20Jordan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdd%20on%20the%20%24166%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-airlines-flying-new-seating-boarding-a-list-status-chase-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20flight%20between%20the%20two%20cities%2C%20%2433%20in%20local%20transit%20costs%2C%20and%20some%20%24900%20for%20a%20flight%20back%20to%20Buenos%20Aires%2C%20and%20the%20total%20is%20approaching%20five%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228dcab040-2470-4b36-901d-45f405cb8187%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20World%20Cup%20dynamic%20pricing%20works%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFIFA%20is%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-dynamic-pricing-surge-cost-fatigue-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edynamic%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20this%20year's%20World%20Cup%2C%20which%20means%20ticket%20prices%20have%20varied%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20FIFA%20said%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bfocused%20on%20ensuring%20fair%20access%20to%20our%20game%20for%20existing%20and%20prospective%20fans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFIFA's%20variable%20pricing%20ticketing%20approach%20aligns%20with%20industry%20trends%20across%20various%20sports%20and%20entertainment%20sectors%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20it%20offered%201%2C000%20tickets%20at%20%2460%20each%20for%20each%20match%2C%20distributed%20by%20each%20participating%20country's%20governing%20body%20for%20the%20sport%20and%20allocated%20to%20loyal%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArgentina%20is%20ranked%20third%20in%20the%20world%20and%20among%20the%20favorites%20to%20win%2C%20while%20many%20also%20expect%20this%20tournament%20to%20be%20the%20last%20in%20which%20fans%20can%20see%20arguably%20soccer's%20greatest%20player%20of%20all%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finter-miami-messi-game-experience-cost-review-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELionel%20Messi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20before%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20it%20is%20much%20cheaper%20to%20see%20some%20of%20the%20smaller%20teams%2C%20which%20have%20little%20hope%20of%20getting%20past%20the%20group%20stage%2C%20let%20alone%20reaching%20the%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20cheapest%20resale%20ticket%20available%20on%20Thursday%20for%20Cape%20Verde%20vs.%20Saudi%20Arabia%20was%20%24126.51.%20The%20two%20teams%20are%20ranked%2061st%20and%2069th%20in%20the%20world%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20story%20is%20part%20of%20our%20%3Cstrong%3ECost%20of%20the%20World%20Cup%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20series%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20sky-high%20prices%20associated%20with%20attending%20the%202026%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%2C%20taking%20place%20from%20June%2011%20to%20July%2019%20across%2016%20cities%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20attending%20the%20World%20Cup%20and%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520rshahidi%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ershahidi%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2255563bed-3481-4628-9e03-691fb66c4572%5C%22%3EThe%20cost%20of%20going%20to%20the%20World%20Cup%20final%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20you%20were%20a%20particularly%20loyal%20supporter%20of%20Argentina's%20soccer%20team%2C%20determined%20to%20see%20every%20game%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20witnessing%20Messi%20lift%20the%20World%20Cup%20trophy%20yet%20again%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20fan%20would%20attend%20five%20more%20games%3A%20the%20round%20of%2032%2C%20the%20round%20of%2016%2C%20quarterfinals%2C%20semifinals%2C%20and%20finals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stay%20in%20Dallas%20would%20last%20another%20three%20nights%2C%20bringing%20the%20hotel%20costs%20to%20about%20%243%2C800.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresuming%20Argentina%20wins%20their%20group%2C%20they%20would%20play%20their%20first%20knockout%20game%20in%20the%20round%20of%2032%20in%20Miami%20on%20July%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20here%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20game%20ticket%20starts%20to%20balloon.%20The%20cheapest%20available%20was%20just%20over%20%242%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FExNyI%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20step%20line%20chart%20shows%20the%20costs%20of%20attending%20each%20of%20Argentina's%20World%20Cup%20games%20on%20a%20potential%20route%20to%20the%20final%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FExNyI%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMiami%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20cities%20for%20local%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-cup-transport-ticket-prices-sky-high-new-york-boston-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etransit%20during%20the%20World%20Cup%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Brightline%2C%20the%20high-speed%20train%20operator%2C%20is%20charging%20%24141%20for%20a%20round-trip%20between%20downtown%20Miami%20and%20Aventura%2C%20the%20closest%20station%20to%20Hard%20Rock%20Stadium.%20That's%20over%20five%20times%20as%20expensive%20as%20on%20a%20normal%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArgentina's%20route%20would%20then%20continue%20to%20Atlanta%2C%20then%20Kansas%20City%20for%20the%20quarter-finals%2C%20back%20to%20Atlanta%20for%20the%20semis%2C%20before%20the%20final%20at%20the%20MetLife%20Stadium%20in%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cheapest%20domestic%20flights%20between%20each%20of%20the%20host%20cities%20ranged%20from%20%24136%20to%20%24198.%20A%20fan%20would%20spend%20roughly%20%24700%20to%20fly%20between%20host%20cities%20throughout%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cheapest%20ticket%20for%20the%20semi-finals%20was%20about%20%242%2C500%2C%20while%20the%20final%20cost%20nearly%20%246%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20to%20the%20stadium%20will%20cost%20%2498%20for%20a%20round-trip%20train%20ticket%20from%20Manhattan's%20Penn%20Station.%20NJ%20Transit%20originally%20announced%20this%20price%20at%20%24150%20before%20lowering%20it%20thanks%20to%20advertising%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%2C%20following%20Argentina%20to%20the%20final%20would%20cost%20around%20%2431%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20particularly%20striking%20when%20considering%20that%20Argentina's%20GDP%20per%20capita%20is%20roughly%20%2414%2C300.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22LUSAIL%20CITY%2C%20QATAR%20-%20DECEMBER%2018%3A%20Lionel%20Messi%20of%20Argentina%20lifts%20the%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20Qatar%202022%20Winner's%20Trophy%20during%20the%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20Qatar%202022%20Final%20match%20between%20Argentina%20and%20France%20at%20Lusail%20Stadium%20on%20December%2018%2C%202022%20in%20Lusail%20City%2C%20Qatar.%20(Photo%20by%20Julian%20Finney%2FGetty%20Images)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a199175b4fb977f3598178a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELionel%20Messi%20lifted%20the%202022%20World%20Cup%20trophy%20in%20Qatar.%3Cp%3EJulian%20Finney%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283323ab1-215d-4dd1-921b-3da0a1e0cf9e%5C%22%3EThe%20cost%20of%20following%20France%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20cheaper%20to%20follow%20France%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20big%20game%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20by%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20benefit%20is%20that%20most%20of%20France's%20games%20are%20scheduled%20in%20a%20smaller%20area.%20France's%20group%20stage%20games%20are%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20Philadelphia%2C%20and%20Boston.%20It's%20the%20same%20three%20cities%20for%20the%20first%20three%20knockout%20rounds.%20The%20final%20is%20at%20New%20Jersey's%20MetLife%20Stadium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20our%20hypothetical%20fan%20could%20base%20themselves%20in%20New%20York%2C%20spending%20%246%2C700%20on%20a%20hotel%20for%20almost%20a%20monthlong%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraveling-on-amtrak-train-first-time-surprising-things-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmtrak%20rail%20tickets%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20cities%20ranged%20from%20%2425%20to%20%24103%20when%20looking%20in%20early%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20then%20be%20a%20%24218%20flight%20to%20Dallas%20for%20the%20semi-final%2C%20plus%20a%20%241%2C000%20hotel%2C%20then%20back%20to%20New%20York%2C%20and%20another%20%241%2C700%20in%20hotel%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20the%20local%20transit%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20including%20an%20%2480%20rail%20ticket%20in%20Boston%20%E2%80%94%20and%20game%20tickets%2C%20which%20are%20similar%20to%20Argentina's%2C%20the%20figure%20reaches%20%2425%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Team%20France%20fan%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20lock%20down%20free%20accommodation%20in%20New%20York%20City%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20tournament%2C%20their%20spend%20would%20decrease%20dramatically%2C%20coming%20out%20closer%20to%20%2416%2C721.%20That's%20nearly%20half%20the%20hypothetical%20spending%20of%20the%20Argentina%20fan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffifa-world-cup-ticket-price-travel-cost-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780304461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a199a152e5a80cfe0500884%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffifa-world-cup-ticket-price-travel-cost-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fans%20face%20high%20costs%20for%20the%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%202026%2C%20with%20some%20fans%20potentially%20spending%20over%20%2430%2C000%20to%20attend%20the%20whole%20tournament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40businessinsider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tokenmaxxing%20is%20entering%20its%20efficiency-maxxing%20era%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223761%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20laptop%20with%20Claude%20Code%20AI%20stickers.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19dd1cb4fb977f35981e49%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222509%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnthropic's%20Claude%20Code%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20AI%20coding%20tools.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20closed%20an%20AI%20use%20leaderboard%2C%20and%20Uber's%20COO%20has%20questioned%20the%20ROI%20on%20token%20spending.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGitHub%20is%20moving%20to%20usage-based%20pricing%20as%20AI%20bills%20come%20due%20for%20token-hungry%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20see%20it%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20an%20AI%20bubble.%20Others%20see%20it%20as%20a%20healthy%20recalibration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20came%20tokenmaxxing.%20Now%20comes%20efficiency-maxxing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilicon%20Valley%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokenmaxxing-ai-token-leaderboards-debate-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eencouraging%20workers%20to%20use%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20through%20gamified%20internal%20leaderboards%20that%20measure%20how%20many%20tokens%20%E2%80%94%20the%20units%20of%20data%20processed%20by%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20they%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20playtime%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20world%20is%20having%20a%20big%20debate%20about%20whether%20tokenmaxxing%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20using%20lots%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-spending-roi-concerns-tokenmaxxing-uber-coo-andrew-macdonald-reaction-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20tokens%20to%20boost%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20gotten%20out%20of%20control.%20It%20has%20also%20got%20executives%20wondering%20when%20the%20return%20on%20investment%20will%20start%20to%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-leaderboard-tokenmaxxing-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20closed%20an%20internal%20dashboard%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20tracked%20AI%20use%20after%20some%20staff%20performed%20tasks%20just%20to%20climb%20the%20leaderboard%2C%20the%20Financial%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlease%20don't%20use%20AI%20just%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20using%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Dave%20Treadwell%2C%20an%20Amazon%20senior%20vice%20president%2C%20told%20staff.%20%26quot%3BUse%20AI%20to%20help%20you%20solve%20customer%20problems%2C%20to%20help%20you%20solve%20business%20problems%2C%20to%20innovate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20employees%20set%20up%20the%20unofficial%20dashboard%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%20to%20%26quot%3Bdrive%20awareness%26quot%3B%20of%20how%20AI%20can%20accelerate%20work%20and%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bwas%20never%20intended%20to%20promote%20the%20use%20of%20AI%20for%20usage's%20sake.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20isn't%20alone%20in%20recalibrating%20on%20AI%20use.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-coo-andrew-macdonald-ai-token-spending-harder-justify-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber's%20COO%2C%20Andrew%20Macdonald%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20released%20in%20late%20May%20that%20he%20has%20yet%20to%20see%20improvements%20directly%20linked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokenmaxxing-debate-uber-exec-viral-ai-costs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eincreased%20AI%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20AI%20skeptics%20see%20these%20as%20signs%20of%20a%20bubble%20as%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%20look%20to%20go%20public%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20enough%20other%20companies%20report%20the%20same%2C%20the%20bubble%20pops%2C%26quot%3B%20Gary%20Marcus%2C%20an%20AI%20researcher%20and%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20wrote%20on%20X%20last%20week%20about%20Uber's%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fbafcb2d-a27e-4c26-af8f-88d9e8ab657f%5C%22%3ETech%20giants%20want%20to%20reduce%20their%20AI%20bills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20execs%20worried%20about%20AI%20costs%2C%20the%20tech%20industry%20has%20mixed%20signs%20about%20how%20it%20might%20play%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20Microsoft's%20GitHub%20Copilot%2C%20an%20AI-powered%20coding%20assistant%2C%20is%20moving%20from%20a%20fixed%20monthly%20payment%20to%20usage-based%20billing.%20In%20an%20April%20blog%20post%2C%20GitHub%20said%20it%20had%20so%20far%20absorbed%20much%20of%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20its%20technology%2C%20and%20the%20fixed%20pricing%20model%20is%20%26quot%3Bno%20longer%20sustainable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20joins%20others%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-code-price-confusion-sam-altman-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic%20and%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20moving%20away%20from%20flat-rate%20seats%20to%20usage-based%20billing%20for%20business%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20price%20changes%20have%20irked%20some%20developers%2C%20investors%20say%20it's%20a%20necessary%20move%20and%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20market%20maturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20past%20year%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20products%20were%20effectively%20subsidizing%20usage%20in%20the%20race%20for%20growth.%20Now%20the%20bill%20is%20showing%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Barry%20Downes%2C%20the%20managing%20partner%20at%20investment%20firm%20Sure%20Valley%20Ventures%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20healthy%20transition%2C%20not%20a%20warning%20sign%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Uber%20COO%20Andrew%20Macdonald.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a17361d2ab5f9757add504d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUber%20COO%20Andrew%20Macdonald's%20comments%20sparked%20a%20debate%20over%20tokenmaxxing.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20coin%2C%20costs%20could%20come%20down%20over%20time%20as%20AI%20companies%20develop%20more%20efficient%20models%20and%20use%20them%20to%20gain%20a%20competitive%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%2C%20for%20example%2C%20says%20its%20latest%20Gemini%203.5%20Flash%20model%20rivals%20frontier%20offerings%20at%20a%20lower%20price%2C%20as%20does%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-surpasses-openai-with-965b-valuation-debuts-opus-4-8-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%20latest%20Opus%204.8%20model%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20Business%20Insider's%20Hugh%20Langley%20reports%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-cost-tokens-gemini-flash-openai-anthropic-gemini-search-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20has%20a%20strong%20position%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20reduce%20costs%20because%20it%20owns%20the%20full%20stack%20%E2%80%94%20chips%2C%20data%20centers%2C%20cloud%2C%20models%2C%20and%20many%20big%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20AI%20labs%20competing%20on%20intelligence%2C%20they're%20now%20competing%20on%20intelligence%20per%20dollar%2C%20with%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20others%20offering%20smaller%2C%20more%20efficient%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22705cef06-09ed-4caa-99e1-23e000c022bf%5C%22%3ETokenmaxxing%20faces%20a%20'necessary%20reality%20check'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOded%20Tahori%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Jeen.ai%2C%20has%20been%20following%20the%20shift%20away%20from%20tokenmaxxing%2C%20as%20his%20own%20startup%20helps%20organizations%20deploy%20AI%20and%20manage%20token%20spend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20tokenmaxxing%20craze%20stemmed%20from%20%26quot%3BFOMO%26quot%3B%20and%20companies%20not%20understanding%20the%20full%20challenge%20of%20building%20with%20AI.%20Now%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20focus%20is%20shifting%20to%20connecting%20spend%20to%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20they%20should%20have%20goals%20about%20budgets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20a%20reason%20why%20to%20spend%20the%20money%3A%20if%20you%20want%20to%20spend%20a%20million%20on%20tokens%2C%20you%20should%20do%20something%20good%20with%20that%20in%20your%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggested%20rewarding%20employees%20who%20use%20AI%20to%20build%20things%20that%20benefit%20the%20company%20with%20a%20larger%20token%20budget%20and%20cutting%20the%20budget%20for%20those%20who%20might%20be%20%26quot%3Bharming%26quot%3B%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20already%20implement%20incentive%20schemes%20that%20prioritize%20results%20over%20output.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvisa-says-its-burning-through-one-trillion-ai-tokens-month-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVisa%20rewards%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20use%20AI%20to%20supercharge%20their%20work%20with%20internal%20%26quot%3Bpoints%26quot%3B%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20buy%20things%20like%20a%20coffee%20maker%2C%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Mills%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20ACF%20Investors%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20tokenmaxxing%20debate%20feels%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bsensible%20check%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20utility%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20a%20sign%20of%20an%20impending%20bubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTokenmaxxing%20artificially%20distorts%20usage%20statistics%20for%20non-productive%20reasons%2C%20so%20a%20clampdown%20is%20a%20constructive%20step%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20serves%20as%20a%20necessary%20reality%20check%2C%20reminding%20organizations%20that%20deploying%20these%20AI%20tools%20carries%20a%20very%20real%20infrastructure%20cost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoken-reckoning-amazon-uber-reassess-ai-investments-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780304404000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19dd4a2ab5f9757add69bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoken-reckoning-amazon-uber-reassess-ai-investments-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amazon%20and%20Uber%20recalibrate%20AI%20usage%20as%20tokenmaxxing%2C%20a%20trend%20of%20excessive%20AI%20use%2C%20sparks%20debate%20on%20productivity%20and%20cost%20efficiency.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rscammell%40businessinsider.com%20(Robert%20Scammell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%20major%20student-loan%20changes%20for%20millions%20of%20borrowers%20are%20a%20month%20away%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225620%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1845712ab5f9757add55d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223747%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20student-loan%20repayment%20overhaul%20will%20take%20effect%20in%20July.%3Cp%3EWin%20McNamee%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETrump's%20student-loan%20repayment%20overhaul%20will%20take%20effect%20July%201.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20includes%20new%20repayment%20plans%20and%20borrowing%20caps%20on%20advanced%20degrees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBorrowers%20could%20face%20higher%20monthly%20bills%20and%20federal%20funding%20gaps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-major-repayment-overhaul-big-beautiful-bill-trump-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStudent-loan%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20get%20ready%3A%20big%20changes%20are%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20Department%20of%20Education%20has%20been%20preparing%20to%20implement%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-final-rule-new-plans-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esweeping%20student-loan%20changes%3C%2Fa%3E%20signed%20into%20law%20in%20the%20administration's%20%26quot%3B%20big%20beautiful%26quot%3B%20spending%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20negotiation%2C%20public%20comment%2C%20and%20ongoing%20litigation%2C%20those%20changes%20will%20take%20effect%20on%20July%201.%20They%20include%20a%20new%20repayment%20plan%2C%20borrowing%20caps%20for%20advanced%20degrees%2C%20and%20the%20elimination%20of%20programs%20that%20allow%20students%20and%20parents%20to%20borrow%20the%20full%20cost%20of%20attendance%20for%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20said%20the%20changes%20are%20intended%20to%20simplify%20a%20complex%20student-loan%20repayment%20system%20and%20curb%20excessive%20borrowing.%20However%2C%20borrower%20advocates%20and%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20have%20raised%20concerns%20that%20the%20changes%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-scramble-save-debt-repayment-plan-trump-confusion-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eincrease%20borrowers'%20monthly%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20and%20lead%20some%20toward%20riskier%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-communications-transfers-lawsuits-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprivate%20student-loan%20products%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUndersecretary%20of%20Education%20Nicholas%20Kent%20said%20in%20an%20April%20statement%20that%20the%20repayment%20overhaul%20%26quot%3Baddresses%20longstanding%20challenges%20in%20higher%20education%20and%20federal%20student%20lending%2C%20including%20exorbitant%20tuition%20costs%2C%20unchecked%20borrowing%2C%20and%20a%20confusing%20maze%20of%20repayment%20options%20that%20too%20often%20leave%20borrowers%20with%20higher%20balances%20despite%20making%20payments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20key%20changes%20coming%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSeATa4iQeOzHtXhvcsvVIBfQLs3uacbq2N6OSrC5Eti5s6i1A%2Fviewform%3Fembedded%3Dtrue%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221073%5C%22%3ELoading%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7af1def-9296-4b33-8cfa-f1a14189cb03%5C%22%3ENew%20repayment%20plans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-which-borrowers-have-exception-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20student-loan%20repayment%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20be%20rolled%20out%20on%20July%201%3A%20the%20Repayment%20Assistance%20Plan%20and%20a%20tiered%20standard%20repayment%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERAP%20is%20intended%20to%20replace%20existing%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%2C%20but%20its%20terms%20are%20less%20generous.%20A%20borrower's%20monthly%20payment%20under%20RAP%20would%20scale%20with%20their%20adjusted%20gross%20income%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eranging%20from%201%25%20to%2010%25%20of%20AGI.%20That's%20different%20from%20income-based%20repayment%20plans%2C%20which%20set%20aside%20a%20portion%20of%20a%20borrower's%20income%20for%20basic%20monthly%20expenses%20and%20calculate%20the%20monthly%20payment%20based%20on%20the%20lower%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20forgiveness%20terms%20for%20RAP%20differ%20from%20those%20of%20existing%20plans.%20While%20current%20income-based%20plans%20allow%20forgiveness%20after%2020%20or%2025%20years%20of%20payments%2C%20RAP%20would%20discharge%20loans%20after%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20is%20also%20rolling%20out%20a%20tiered%20standard%20plan%20on%20July%201.%20Under%20this%20plan%2C%20borrowers%20would%20repay%20their%20loans%20in%20full%20over%20a%20repayment%20period%20based%20on%20the%20amount%20of%20their%20principal%20balance%2C%20with%20a%20minimum%20payment%20of%20%2450%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20borrowers%20with%20a%20balance%20of%20less%20than%20%2425%2C000%20would%20have%20a%2010-year%20repayment%20period%2C%20while%20those%20with%20a%20balance%20of%20%24100%2C000%20or%20more%20would%20have%20a%2025-year%20repayment%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20who%20take%20out%20their%20first%20student%20loans%20on%20or%20after%20July%201%20will%20have%20access%20to%20only%20RAP%20and%20the%20tiered%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2243650ef5-d7c2-4d74-bf3e-c53d152bc916%5C%22%3ETransitioning%20off%20the%20SAVE%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-lawsuit-save-plan-immediate-student-loan-forgiveness-borrowers-trump-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20SAVE%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20created%20by%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20to%20give%20borrowers%20cheaper%20monthly%20payments%20and%20a%20shorter%20timeline%20to%20loan%20forgiveness.%20Now%20that%20it's%20been%20eliminated%2C%207%20million%20enrolled%20borrowers%20will%20have%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-plan-student-loan-borrowers-kicked-off-new-email-repayment-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etransition%20off%20the%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20begin%20repayment%20on%20a%20new%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20said%20that%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-plan-student-loan-borrowers-need-more-time-repayment-debt-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebeginning%20on%20July%201%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20servicers%20will%20start%20sending%20notices%20to%20SAVE%20borrowers%20informing%20them%20of%20their%20deadline%20to%20transition%20to%20a%20new%20plan.%20Borrowers%20will%20have%2090%20days%20to%20make%20that%20transition%2C%20and%20if%20they%20do%20not%20take%20any%20action%2C%20their%20servicers%20will%20automatically%20place%20them%20on%20the%20standard%20or%20tiered%20repayment%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20notice%20was%20sent%20to%20SAVE%20borrowers%20in%20late%20May.%20The%20notice%2C%20which%20Business%20Insider%20reviewed%2C%20said%20that%20borrowers%20do%20not%20need%20to%20wait%20until%20July%20to%20switch%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20choosing%20a%20new%20repayment%20plan%20and%20making%20payments%20now%2C%20you'll%20pay%20off%20your%20debt%20more%20quickly%20than%20if%20you%20stay%20on%20the%20SAVE%20Plan%20in%20a%20forbearance%20that's%20adding%20to%20your%20loan%20balance%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20notice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudent-loan%20borrowers%20are%20still%20hoping%20to%20reverse%20the%20ruling%20in%20court.%20In%20March%2C%20four%20borrowers%20%E2%80%94%20represented%20by%20the%20law%20firm%20Public%20Goods%20Practice%20%E2%80%94%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20seeking%20relief%20for%20SAVE%20borrowers%2C%20and%20the%20litigation%20is%20ongoing.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228627e938-3d9f-403e-a5b5-1bae60fd2355%5C%22%3ENew%20borrowing%20caps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20debate%20in%20Trump's%20repayment%20overhaul%20was%20over%20new%20borrowing%20caps%20on%20advanced%20degrees.%20The%20Department%20of%20Education%20will%20implement%20a%20%24100%2C000%20lifetime%20borrowing%20cap%20for%20graduate%20students%20and%20a%20%24200%2C000%20lifetime%20cap%20for%20professional%20students.%20The%20department%20is%20also%20limiting%20the%20professional%20cap%20to%2011%20programs%2C%20including%20medicine%2C%20dentistry%2C%20and%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Parent%20PLUS%20program%20will%20also%20face%20new%20caps.%20While%20it%20previously%20allowed%20parents%20to%20borrow%20the%20full%20cost%20of%20attendance%20for%20their%20kids'%20programs%2C%20parent%20borrowers%20will%20face%20a%20%2465%2C000%20borrowing%20cap%20for%20each%20child%20beginning%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%2C%20borrowers%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-overhaul-bipartisan-bill-nurses-borrowing-caps-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elawmakers%20across%20the%20aisle%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20pushing%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20to%20change%20its%20definition%20of%20a%20professional%20degree%20to%20include%20advanced%20nursing%20programs.%20While%20the%20department%20has%20said%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20nursing%20programs%20would%20fall%20into%20the%20lower%20borrowing%20cap%2C%2025%20Democratic-led%20states%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-states-lawsuit-borrowing-caps-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20recent%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20limits%20would%20exacerbate%20the%20ongoing%20healthcare%20worker%20shortage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigher%20education%20is%20expensive%2C%20and%20our%20health%20care%20system%20is%20already%20under%20immense%20strain%2C%26quot%3B%20Letitia%20James%2C%20New%20York's%20attorney%20general%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20alongside%20the%20lawsuit.%20%26quot%3BThis%20rule%20will%20shut%20talented%20people%20out%20of%20critical%20professions%20and%20leave%20communities%20with%20fewer%20health%20care%20providers%20they%20desperately%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20student%20loans%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520asheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-july-changes-borrowers-save-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780304403000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a184580b4fb977f35980a97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-july-changes-borrowers-save-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20new%20repayment%20plans%20to%20borrowing%20caps%2C%20millions%20of%20federal%20student-loan%20borrowers%20will%20start%20to%20see%20key%20changes%20beginning%20in%20July.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20a%20lawyer%20at%20OpenAI%20uses%20OpenAI%20at%20work%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221254%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20AI-generated%20image%20shows%20a%20woman%20wearing%20brown%20glasses%20and%20a%20cream%20sweater%20smiles%20in%20an%20office.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a184b75b4fb977f35980ace%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22941%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20lawyer%20Nicole%20Diaz%20is%20also%20a%20ChatGPT%20power%20user.%20She%20used%20it%20to%20create%20this%20headshot.%3Cp%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInside%20OpenAI%2C%20even%20the%20lawyers%20are%20starting%20to%20build%20tools%20for%20themselves.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENicole%20Diaz%20is%20an%20associate%20general%20counsel%20who%20uses%20ChatGPT%20and%20Codex%20to%20help%20simplify%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20tool%20she%20built%20turns%20jargon-ridden%20law-firm%20memos%20into%20plain-English%20policies%20for%20employees%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20Diaz%20had%20never%20written%20code.%20Then%20she%20joined%20OpenAI's%20legal%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20the%20associate%20general%20counsel%20now%20uses%20OpenAI's%20apps%20to%20simplify%20and%20speed%20her%20legal%20work.%20She%20has%20built%20tools%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-staff-6-tips-chatgpt-model-smarter-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Codex%2C%20the%20company's%20coding%20agent%2C%20to%20help%20turn%20dense%20law-firm%20memos%20into%20plain-English%20policies%2C%20triage%20employee%20email%2C%20draft%20replies%2C%20and%20track%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20sense%20of%20what's%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Diaz%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20rapidly%20expanded%20in%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%20even%20three%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiaz%20works%20in%20corporate%20compliance%2C%20a%20legal%20function%20focused%20not%20on%20the%20products%20OpenAI%20puts%20into%20the%20world%2C%20but%20on%20how%20the%20company%20conducts%20business%2C%20making%20sure%20employees%20follow%20the%20law%20and%20ethical%20standards.%20It's%20also%20the%20kind%20of%20function%20companies%20tend%20to%20build%20out%20as%20they%20prepare%20for%20the%20scrutiny%20that%20comes%20with%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ipo-racing-to-go-public-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIPO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Diaz%20has%20been%20using%20OpenAI's%20technology%20to%20make%20that%20work%20faster%20and%20easier%20to%20manage.%20The%20tools%20do%20not%20replace%20her%20judgment%2C%20she%20said.%20They%20absorb%20the%20repetitive%20work%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20judgment%20was%20shaped%20by%20a%20traditional%20legal%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20She%20learned%20the%20law%20at%20Harvard%20and%20the%20machinery%20of%20high-stakes%20litigation%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskadden-david-goldschmidt-retires-career-advice-ai-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESkadden%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20she%20worked%20as%20an%20associate.%20Later%2C%20she%20moved%20into%20the%20client%20side%20as%20a%20compliance%20lawyer%20at%20Snap.%20None%20of%20those%20places%20taught%20her%20to%20build%20software.%20OpenAI%20changed%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20way%2C%20Diaz%20is%20the%20target%20of%20OpenAI's%20pitch.%20The%20company%20is%20betting%20that%20artificial-intelligence%20agents%20can%20turn%20workers%20who%20never%20saw%20themselves%20as%20builders%20into%20people%20who%20make%20their%20own%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20way%20of%20working%20also%20offers%20a%20window%20into%20a%20live%20debate%20in%20legal%20tech.%20As%20law%20firms%20and%20corporate%20legal%20teams%20weigh%20whether%20to%20buy%20specialized%20legal%20software%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-versus-openai-chatgpt-for-lawyers-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Diaz%20shows%20what%20lawyers%20can%20do%20using%20frontier%20models%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cec5115f-71c2-404f-8fab-9112c52d131b%5C%22%3EA%20magic%20wand%20for%20policy-writing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20place%20Diaz%20put%20ChatGPT%20to%20work%20was%20one%20of%20the%20least%20glamorous%20parts%20of%20corporate%20compliance%3A%20policy%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20firms%20often%20send%20over%20policies%20thick%20with%20legal%20jargon%20and%20ten-dollar%20words%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20of%20document%20that%20might%20work%20at%20a%20more%20bureaucratic%20company%2C%20Diaz%20said%2C%20but%20not%20at%20OpenAI.%20She%20used%20to%20rewrite%20those%20policies%20by%20hand%2C%20turning%20them%20into%20guidance%20employees%20could%20actually%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20created%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-staff-6-tips-chatgpt-model-smarter-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20skill%20for%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkills%20let%20users%20turn%20a%20repeatable%20task%20into%20a%20set%20of%20instructions%20they%20can%20reuse%2C%20so%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20write%20a%20lengthy%20prompt%20each%20time.%20Diaz%20created%20a%20skill%20she%20called%20%26quot%3Bsimplify.%26quot%3B%20Its%20job%20is%20to%20take%20legal%20policies%20and%20shorten%20sentences%2C%20cut%20legalese%2C%20and%20match%20the%20format%20of%20OpenAI's%20policy%20templates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiaz%20still%20reviews%20the%20output%20herself%20and%20sends%20policies%20back%20to%20outside%20counsel%20for%20their%20approval.%20But%20she%20said%20the%20skill%20gets%20her%20to%20a%20workable%20draft%20much%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281e3441b-8128-4ee3-885d-3eb61cbd580b%5C%22%3ECodex%20as%20a%20coworker%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20often%20come%20to%20Diaz%20with%20questions%20about%20whether%20they%20need%20approval%20to%20take%20an%20advisory%20role%2C%20invest%20in%20a%20friend's%20startup%2C%20or%20attend%20a%20fancy%20dinner%20with%20a%20government%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%2C%20Diaz%20said%2C%20she%20relied%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-ai-ceo-interviews-google-docs-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Doc%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20draft%20responses%20for%20different%20types%20of%20asks.%20She%20still%20had%20to%20decide%20which%20guidance%20applied%2C%20write%20a%20response%2C%20and%20keep%20track%20of%20how%20the%20question%20was%20handled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Diaz%20uses%20Codex%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20artificial%20intelligence%20that%20can%20carry%20out%20tasks%20with%20little%20hand-holding%20%E2%80%94%20to%20help%20triage.%20Every%20day%20at%205%20p.m.%2C%20the%20system%20scans%20her%20inbox%20for%20emails%20about%20conflicts%2C%20sorts%20them%20by%20risk%2C%20and%20drafts%20replies%20based%20on%20her%20pre-written%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221532%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Codex%20automation%20page%20shows%20instructions%20for%20a%20%26quot%3BDaily%20conflicts%20triage%26quot%3B%20task%20and%20a%20status%20message%20saying%20it%20has%20been%20working%20for%2021%20seconds.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19994cb4fb977f359817cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22766%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20of%20the%20instructions%20she%20gives%20Codex%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bconflicts%20triage%26quot%3B%20workflow.%3Cp%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20employee%20who%20asks%20about%20angel%20investing%20might%20get%20a%20standard%20response.%20Another%20who%20wants%20to%20join%20a%20trade%20association%20that%20also%20does%20lobbying%20might%20get%20a%20response%20asking%20for%20more%20information.%20Higher-risk%20disclosures%20are%20flagged%20for%20Diaz's%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20also%20keeps%20a%20log%20of%20the%20types%20of%20disclosures%20she%20receives%2C%20how%20she%20responds%2C%20and%20how%20long%20it%20takes%20to%20respond%2C%20giving%20her%20a%20better%20view%20of%20where%20employees%20are%20getting%20stuck%20and%20where%20OpenAI's%20policies%20may%20need%20to%20be%20clearer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294f66fc8-199e-4908-bcf9-c69dd84e2895%5C%22%3EShe's%20got%20(ChatGPT)%20skills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tools%20still%20need%20work.%20One%20of%20Diaz's%20biggest%20complaints%20is%20that%20their%20responses%20can%20sound%20too%20%26quot%3Blawyerly.%26quot%3B%20She's%20working%20on%20an%20%26quot%3Babout%20me%26quot%3B%20file%20that%20tells%20ChatGPT%20how%20she%20writes%20and%20talks%2C%20so%20she%20can%20plug%20it%20into%20different%20skills%20and%20make%20the%20output%20sound%20more%20like%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20kind%20of%20thing%20they%20teach%20at%20law%20school.%20At%20OpenAI%2C%20learning%20to%20build%20seems%20to%20happen%20almost%20through%20osmosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20expectation%20that%20every%20lawyer%20suddenly%20becomes%20a%20Codex%20power%20user.%20Diaz%20credits%20a%20colleague%2C%20Bright%20Kellogg%2C%20with%20helping%20lead%20the%20legal%20team%20through%20a%20gentler%20kind%20of%20change%20management%3A%20sharing%20small%20lessons%20each%20week%20and%20highlighting%20examples%20of%20what%20other%20lawyers%20are%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Diaz%2C%20that%20peer%20learning%20has%20become%20part%20of%20the%20fun.%20Seeing%20other%20people's%20tools%20can%20feel%2C%20she%20said%2C%20like%20trading%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%3A%20one%20person%20has%20a%20skill%20with%20%26quot%3Breally%20cool%20powers%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20someone%20else%20wants%20to%20try%20it%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-openai-lawyer-nicole-diaz-uses-ai-for-legal-work-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780304402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a184b75b4fb977f35980ace%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-openai-lawyer-nicole-diaz-uses-ai-for-legal-work-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22B